  "claim_short": "The packet proves that a bounded nilpotent Hilbert-space operator \\(N\\) of finite nilpotency order cannot satisfy \\[ |N| \\leq |\\operatorname{Re} N| \\] unless \\(N=0\\). The proof uses the Haagerup--de la Harpe numerical-radius bound for nilpotents: \\[ w(N) \\leq \\|N\\|\\cos\\frac{\\pi}{m+1}, \\qquad N^m=0. \\] The Fong-Tsui inequality gives the reverse lower chain \\[ \\|N\\| \\leq \\|\\operatorname{Re}N\\| \\leq w(N), \\] which is...",
